# Code Style Guidelines

This document defines the code style guidelines for the folder-web project.

## HTML Style

- Use proper indentation (2 spaces)
- Use lowercase for HTML element names, attributes, and attribute values
- Quote all attribute values using double quotes
- Close all HTML tags properly
- Use semantic HTML5 elements (header, nav, main, section, article, footer)
- Include proper meta tags for responsive design:
  ```html
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  ```

## CSS Style

- Use proper indentation (2 spaces)
- Write one selector per line
- Include a space after property name's colon
- End all declarations with a semicolon
- Use shorthand properties where possible
- Group related properties together
- Use a mobile-first approach with media queries
- Example:
  ```css
  .selector {
    property: value;
    property2: value;
  }
  
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .selector {
      property: value;
    }
  }
  ```

## JavaScript Style

- Use proper indentation (2 spaces)
- Use semicolons after statements
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Comment code appropriately
- Avoid global variables
- Example:
  ```javascript
  function calculateTotal(price, quantity) {
    const total = price * quantity;
    return total;
  }
  ```

## Responsive Design

- Start with mobile design first, then enhance for larger screens
- Use relative units (%, em, rem) instead of absolute units (px) when appropriate
- Test on multiple device sizes and browsers
- Use breakpoints consistently throughout the project
